                            <comment id="370210" author="adilger" created="Fri, 21 Apr 2023 22:57:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve also filed &lt;a href=&quot;https://savannah.gnu.org/bugs/?64088&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://savannah.gnu.org/bugs/?64088&lt;/a&gt; &quot;find should support file attribute flags (immutable, append-only, fscrypt, etc.)&quot; for upstream find, so that we might use the same option names, but I don&apos;t have high hopes on it getting implemented any time soon.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="370207" author="adilger" created="Fri, 21 Apr 2023 22:27:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It would also be useful to be able to print the file attribute flags with &quot;&lt;tt&gt;-printf %La&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; or similar, and they would print a comma-separated list of named attribute flags, and hex value of any unknown attributes.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
